            "type": "text",
            "text": "Key Factors Influencing Kokoro Latency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Kokoro latency is impacted by several technical elements, including model size, inference hardware, and network overhead. For instance, larger model variants may increase latency, while optimized GPU configurations can mitigate it. Teams should profile their specific deployment to identify bottlenecks, such as CPU throttling or memory bandwidth limits, which directly affect response times."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Deployment Strategies to Minimize Latency"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "To reduce Kokoro latency, consider containerization with lightweight runtimes and auto-scaling policies that match traffic patterns. Use batch processing judiciously—smaller batch sizes often lower per-request latency but may increase overhead. Implementing edge caching for frequent queries can also offload inference tasks, cutting down end-to-end delays."
          }
        ]
      },
